excerpt: Founded in 1894, this hilltop center with giant telescopes offers tours, solar viewing & stargazing.
detail_description: Lowell Observatory, established in 1894 by Percival Lowell, is a renowned hilltop center dedicated to the study of astronomy and solar system evolution. The observatory offers tours, solar viewing, and stargazing opportunities for over 100,000 annual visitors. Home to several telescopes and the Navy Precision Optical Interferometer, it also conducts pure research in astronomical phenomena.
name: Lowell Observatory
address: 1400 W Mars Hill Rd, Flagstaff, AZ 86001, USA

excerpt: Museum chronicling the Colorado Plateau from 15,000 B.C. to the present via exhibits & artifacts.
detail_description: The Museum of Northern Arizona offers a comprehensive look at the history and culture of the Colorado Plateau, spanning from 15,000 B.C. to the present day through its exhibits and artifacts. Established nearly a century ago, the museum has deep roots in preserving Native American artifacts and culture with early employees being local Indigenous people. Collaborating with members of 42 Colorado Plateau tribes, the museum's exhibitions are carefully curated to provide historical and cultural context for objects and photographs.
name: Museum of Northern Arizona
address: 3101 N Fort Valley Rd, Flagstaff, AZ 86001, USA

excerpt: Expansive, curved canyon featuring trails & stairs past ruins of Sinagua cliff dwellings.
detail_description: Walnut Canyon National Monument, located less than 9 miles east of downtown Flagstaff, offers a glimpse into the ancient cliff dwellings of the Sinagua people who inhabited the area from 600 to 1400 AD. The main cliff dwellings feature structures carved and built from local stone and mortar, showcasing the resilience of these ancient inhabitants.
name: Walnut Canyon National Monument
address: Arizona, USA

excerpt: Flagstaff is a city in the U.S. state of Arizona, surrounded by mountains, desert and ponderosa pine forests. It’s a gateway to the San Francisco Peaks, home to Arizona’s tallest mountain (Humphreys Peak) and the Arizona Snowbowl ski resort. Nearby, Wupatki National Monument has Native American pueblo sites, and Walnut Canyon National Monument is dotted with their cliff dwellings.
detail_description: Flagstaff, a city in Arizona, is surrounded by mountains, desert, and pine forests. It serves as a gateway to the San Francisco Peaks and is home to the Arizona Snowbowl ski resort. Nearby attractions include Wupatki National Monument with Native American pueblo sites and Walnut Canyon National Monument with cliff dwellings. The High Country Motor Lodge offers a stylish retro experience with modern amenities like Nordic-style spa facilities and a restaurant serving made-to-order meals.
name: Flagstaff
address: Arizona, USA

excerpt: Circa-1904 historic mansion with art nouveau touches covering 13,000 sq. ft., with guided tours.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of a bustling city, Riordan Mansion State Historic Park is a captivating glimpse into Arizona's history. The circa-1904 mansion, spanning 13,000 square feet and adorned with art nouveau elements, offers guided tours for visitors. Once home to the influential Riordan family, known for their contributions to various American industries, this architectural marvel showcases American Arts and Crafts-style design.
name: Riordan Mansion State Historic Park
address: 409 W Riordan Rd, Flagstaff, AZ 86001, USA

excerpt: Facility at Fort Tuthill County Park offering treetop suspended obstacle courses for kids & adults.
detail_description: Flagstaff Extreme Adventure Course, located at Fort Tuthill County Park, offers an exhilarating treetop suspended obstacle course experience for both kids and adults. With courses led by qualified instructors, participants can navigate through over 70 obstacles at heights ranging from 15 to 60 feet above the ground. Additionally, visitors can enjoy the largest zipline course in the Western United States.
name: Flagstaff Extreme Adventure Course
address: Fort Tuthill County Park, 2446 Ft Tuthill Lp, Flagstaff, AZ 86005, USA

excerpt: Headquarters for non-profit organization preserving historic district & organizing events.
detail_description: Downtown Flagstaff is a vibrant hub of activity, offering a variety of experiences for visitors. From independent walking tours to dining at local eateries, exploring attractions, and enjoying the lively bar and brewery scene, there's something for everyone. The area boasts architecturally significant streets like Humphreys and Verde Streets, as well as Route 66 in the south. The historic charm of Downtown Flagstaff attracts those seeking an active social life amidst nostalgic architecture.
name: Downtown Flagstaff
address: 6 E Aspen Ave # 200, Flagstaff, AZ 86001, USA

excerpt: 215-acre park offers a 2-mile hiking loop trail, picnicking space, wildlife & scenic mountain views.
detail_description: Buffalo Park, located just north of downtown Flagstaff, is a 215-acre community park offering a 2-mile hiking loop trail with scenic mountain views and wildlife sightings. Despite the absence of actual buffalo, the park provides an open view of the San Francisco Peaks surrounded by ponderosa pines and tall grasses. It's an ideal spot for outdoor photography, showcasing Flagstaff's beautiful landscape. The park also features a challenge course for those seeking to elevate their exercise routine.
name: Buffalo Park
address: 2400 N Gemini Rd, Flagstaff, AZ 86004, USA

detail_description: Mother Road Brewing Company, established in 2011, draws its name from the moniker given to Route 66 by John Steinbeck. Founded by Michael Marquess and his wife Alissa, along with brewer Urs Riner, the brewery aims to create and distribute exceptional beers while honoring history, community, and the environment. Their taproom features art from local artists and occasionally hosts live music performances.
name: Mother Road Brewing Company
address: 7 S Mikes Pike St, Flagstaff, AZ 86001, USA

detail_description: The Aspen Nature Loop, also known as the Aspen Loop or Aspen Nature Lollipop, is a 2.5-mile trail near Flagstaff offering stunning views of the San Francisco field and even extending to the Grand Canyon. During fall, the loop is adorned with golden aspens, while summer brings an array of wildflowers and diverse bird species. The hike is considered laid-back, rated easy by experienced hikers and moderate by beginners, making it suitable for families and trail runners alike.
name: The Grand Canyon National Park Foundation
address: 625 N Beaver St, Flagstaff, AZ 86001, USA

excerpt: Former hospital built in 1908 housing remnants of northern Arizona's farming & transportation past.
detail_description: The Pioneer Museum, housed in the historic Coconino County Hospital for the Indigent built in 1908, offers a glimpse into northern Arizona's farming and transportation history. The museum features decade rooms spanning from the 1880s to the 1960s, showcasing Flagstaff's evolution over time. Notable exhibits include a 1929 locomotive and a Santa Fe caboose from the 1940s.
name: Pioneer Museum--Arizona Historical Society
address: 2340 N Fort Valley Rd, Flagstaff, AZ 86001, USA

excerpt: Sprawling area with archery & equestrian facilities plus trails, fairgrounds & an adventure course.
detail_description: Fort Tuthill County Park is a vast 15-acre Airforce Recreation Area nestled in Coconino National Forest, surrounded by the world's largest Ponderosa Pine Forest. The park boasts archery and equestrian facilities, fairgrounds, and an exhilarating adventure course at Flagstaff Extreme Adventure. With its friendly staff and access to stunning mountain views, it's a haven for outdoor enthusiasts seeking nature escapades.
name: Fort Tuthill County Park
address: 2446 Ft Tuthill Lp, Flagstaff, AZ 86005, USA

detail_description: Fort Valley, housed in the historic Coconino County Hospital for the Indigent, offers a glimpse into Flagstaff and northern Arizona's rich history. The exhibits showcase various aspects such as ranching, logging, and transportation, providing visitors with an immersive experience of the region's past.
name: Fort Valley (Pioneer Museum)
address: Flagstaff, AZ 86001, USA

excerpt: Conservation area for native high-elevation plants, with views of wildlife & a butterfly garden.
detail_description: Nestled just off historic Route 66, The Arboretum at Flagstaff is a stunning conservation area dedicated to high-elevation native plants. Spanning 200 acres within the world's largest contiguous ponderosa pine forest, this enchanting destination offers visitors a chance to immerse themselves in nature while enjoying breathtaking views of colorful fall foliage. With over 750 species of plants and a delightful butterfly garden, it's an ideal spot for families looking to explore and learn about the unique flora of northern Arizona.
name: The Arboretum at Flagstaff
address: 4001 S Woody Mountain Rd, Flagstaff, AZ 86005, USA

excerpt: Performing arts center built in 1911 & renovated in 2002 hosts musicians & movie screenings.
detail_description: The Orpheum Theater, situated in downtown Flagstaff, is a historic performing arts center that has been a prominent venue since its establishment in 1911. Following a comprehensive renovation in 2002, it now features modern amenities such as plush seating, an expansive balcony area, top-notch sound systems, a full bar, and a lounge.
name: The Orpheum Theater
address: 15 W Aspen Ave, Flagstaff, AZ 86001, USA

excerpt: Casual brewpub serving burgers & other grub, plus handcrafted ales & an extensive whiskey selection.
detail_description: Flagstaff Brewing Company is a casual brewpub located in Flagstaff, offering a variety of handcrafted ales and an extensive selection of whiskey. The pub serves delicious burgers made from range-raised beef sourced locally, along with Belgian-style fries. Despite its limited seating and somewhat tricky location to find, it's considered a rewarding discovery for travelers. Brewer Stu Howe runs the small-scale brewing facility, producing experimental brews for regular customers to enjoy.
name: Flagstaff Brewing Company
address: 16 Historic Rte 66, Flagstaff, AZ 86001, USA

detail_description: Elden Pueblo Archaeological Site, built by the Sinagua tribe between 1070 and 1275 A.D., offers a unique opportunity for public engagement in archaeology. The site contains around 70 rooms and is believed to have been a significant trading center. Visitors can take self-guided tours using available brochures or participate in guided tours and excavations during Public Archaeology Days.
name: Elden Pueblo Archaeological Site
address: US-89, Flagstaff, AZ 86004, USA

detail_description: The Flagstaff Visitor Center, housed in the historic Santa Fe passenger train depot on Route 66, is a one-stop destination for all your travel needs. The friendly and knowledgeable staff are ready to assist with directions, travel planning, dining suggestions, and local history. Visitors can pick up Flagstaff Visitor Guides, 5-Day Explorers guidebooks, event calendars, and area maps.
name: Flagstaff Visitor Center
address: 1 E Rte 66, Flagstaff, AZ 86001, USA

detail_description: Flagstaff Pulliam Airport is located in the beautiful city of Flagstaff, Arizona, known as The City of Seven Wonders. Surrounded by stunning natural landscapes including mountains, deserts, and pine forests, it serves as a gateway to famous attractions such as the Grand Canyon and Sunset Crater National Monument.
name: Flagstaff Pulliam Airport
address: 6200 S Pulliam Dr, Flagstaff, AZ 86005, USA

excerpt: Burger joint known for using local ingredients & English muffins as buns in a modern, casual space.
detail_description: Diablo Burger is a modern and casual burger joint that prides itself on using local ingredients and serving its burgers on English muffins instead of traditional buns. The restaurant is located in an oddly shaped circular building next to an Italian restaurant, offering limited seating but providing a rewarding experience for persistent travelers. The burgers are made from range-raised beef sourced from a local ranch, and all ingredients are obtained from nearby businesses whenever possible.
name: Diablo Burger
address: 120 N Leroux St, Flagstaff, AZ 86001, USA

excerpt: Walking trail featuring scenic overlooks with city views, volcanic rock formations & more.
detail_description: Fatman's Loop Trail is a popular and easily accessible hike in Flagstaff, offering unique views and interesting rock formations. This 2.4-mile trail is frequented by hikers, bikers, and runners, featuring beautiful wildflowers and scenic overlooks of the city's eastern suburbs and countryside. The trail is mostly easy with some steep sections, making it suitable for visitors looking for a less strenuous outdoor experience.
name: Fatman's Loop Trail
address: 5098 US-89, Flagstaff, AZ 86004, USA

detail_description: Located just a mile from downtown, the Coconino Center for the Arts is a hub of creativity in Flagstaff. The center features contemporary art exhibitions in its galleries and hosts live entertainment and concerts in its 200-seat theater. Visitors have praised the diverse and engaging art on display, as well as the community events and local talent showcased at the center. From artist talks to outstanding theatrical performances, this arts center offers a range of cultural experiences for visitors to enjoy.
name: Coconino Center For the Arts
address: 2300 N Fort Valley Rd, Flagstaff, AZ 86001, USA

detail_description: Flagstaff, home to Northern Arizona University (NAU), attracts a diverse crowd of tourists and students. The city is popular among southern Arizona tourists seeking snow and ski adventures, while visitors from across the country stop by on their way to the Grand Canyon. NAU draws many young adults to study in this vibrant town with a strong outdoor culture. Additionally, Flagstaff has become a hub for vanlifers, nomads, and remote workers due to its recreational opportunities.
name: Northern Arizona University
address: S San Francisco St, Flagstaff, AZ 86011, USA

detail_description: Flagstaff Amtrak station, a historic Tudor Revival brick building dating back to 1926, is a significant part of the city's past and present. The trains running regularly to Flagstaff can be heard throughout town with their loud whistles. Besides its historical significance, the station also houses the Visitor Center, making it one of the top attractions in downtown Flagstaff.
name: Flagstaff Amtrak
address: 1 E Rte 66, Flagstaff, AZ 86001, USA

detail_description: Heritage Square is located in the heart of Flagstaff's historic downtown area. The square hosts a variety of events and outdoor movies during the summer months, making it a lively hub for locals and visitors alike. Nearby Wheeler Park offers additional green space to explore, creating a pedestrian-friendly area. The central location also makes it convenient for travelers heading towards the Grand Canyon, with various streets providing easy access to different parts of the city.
name: Heritage Square
address: Flagstaff, AZ 86001, USA

excerpt: Inventive house-brewed beers & unique pub fare offered in hip, industrial digs with a cool bar.
detail_description: Brewery Dark Sky Brewing Co. offers unique pub fare and house-brewed beers in a hip, industrial setting in downtown Flagstaff. The Taproom is popular for pre or post-show drinks, and the beer names are interesting and taste great.
name: Dark Sky Brewing Co.
address: 117 N Beaver St, Flagstaff, AZ 86001, USA

excerpt: Contemporary lounge with a speakeasy vibe offering classic cocktails & a rustic courtyard.
detail_description: The Annex Cocktail Lounge is a contemporary establishment with a speakeasy atmosphere, offering classic cocktails and a rustic courtyard. Originally created to handle overflow from the adjacent Tinderbox Kitchen, it has since become a destination in its own right for cocktails and small plates. The lounge offers inventive seasonal cocktails like the Tell-Tale Heart and Grapefruit Shandy, along with delicious appetizers, beer, and wine in a trendy setting.
name: The Annex Cocktail Lounge
address: 50 S San Francisco St, Flagstaff, AZ 86001, USA

detail_description: FlagTagAZ in Flagstaff, Arizona offers a variety of entertainment options for visitors of all ages. The venue features a multi-level, black-lit laser tag arena where participants can engage in interactive gameplay using high-tech vests and laser tag guns. Additionally, guests can test their skills at axe throwing and enjoy arcade games at the facility. With a pizza cafe serving beer, wine, and mead, FlagTagAZ provides an all-encompassing experience for food and fun.
name: FlagTagAZ
address: 1801 W Rte 66 #102, Flagstaff, AZ 86001, USA

detail_description: If you're looking to make the most of a one-day trip to the Grand Canyon, staying in Downtown Flagstaff is a convenient option. Located just an hour-and-a-half drive from the canyon, it provides easy access to local natural wonders and allows for exploration of nearby attractions. Additionally, downtown offers a range of dining, shopping, and entertainment options within walking distance from your accommodation.
name: Grand Canyon Railway
address: 1201 W Rte 66 #200, Flagstaff, AZ 86001, USA

detail_description: AZ Segway and Pedal Tours, located in the Grand Circle Outpost, offers an exceptional way to explore Flagstaff, Arizona. Their guided tours through the NAU campus and historic Downtown Flagstaff provide a perfect blend of entertainment and education. With no minimum age requirement, these tours are suitable for all ages. Visitors can enjoy free riding time on Segways after the tour to further experience the fun of gliding through the city streets.
name: AZ Segway and Pedal Tours
address: 600 N Thorpe Rd, Flagstaff, AZ 86001, USA

detail_description: Dr. Phillip Williams, MD is a highly regarded Gynecologist in Flagstaff known for his exceptional care and compassion towards his patients. Patients appreciate his promptness, attentive listening, and proactive approach to providing the best possible care. His long-standing staff is also commended for their welcoming and efficient service. Dr. Williams' kind and competent care has earned him high praise from patients who have been under his care for over two decades, emphasizing his compassionate nature and willingness to address all concerns thoroughly.
name: Phillip Williams, MD
address: 1100 N San Francisco St # B, Flagstaff, AZ 86001, USA

detail_description: Nestled in the scenic Fort Tuthill County Park in Flagstaff, Arizona, the Fort Tuthill Military History Museum is a captivating destination for history enthusiasts. Reopened in 2017 after extensive renovations, this museum offers an immersive journey through military heritage.
name: Fort Tuthill Military History Museum
address: 2446 Ft Tuthill Lp, Flagstaff, AZ 86001, USA

excerpt: Buzzy eatery offering wood-fired Neapolitan-style pies with gourmet toppings, plus wine on tap.
detail_description: Fat Olives is a popular dining spot known for its wood-fired Neapolitan-style pizzas with gourmet toppings and wine on tap. The restaurant's wood-fired dome oven, weighing over 3900 pounds, was crafted in Italy and is a key feature of the establishment. Originally starting as a mobile catering company over 25 years ago, Fat Olives was founded by award-winning chef John Conley.
name: Fat Olives
address: 2308 E Rte 66, Flagstaff, AZ 86004, USA

excerpt: Microbrewery offering creative wood-fired pizzas & salads, plus an adjacent billiards hall.
detail_description: Beaver Street Brewery is a popular microbrewery in Flagstaff, known for its creative wood-fired pizzas, salads, and adjacent billiards hall.
name: Beaver Street Brewery
address: 11 S Beaver St #1, Flagstaff, AZ 86001, USA

detail_description: The Flagstaff Symphony Orchestra is an excellent performing arts organization with a long history of operating continuously since 1950. The orchestra regularly stages concerts and provides outreach programs to the community, and it is one of the largest and most active regional symphonies in northern Arizona.
name: Flagstaff Symphony Orchestra
address: 113 E Aspen Ave A, Flagstaff, AZ 86001, USA

detail_description: The starting point, known as the trail head, of Sandy's Canyon Trail offers a scenic and picturesque route for hikers. This particular path presents an opportunity for exploration and adventure, with captivating sights awaiting at every turn. The entrance to this trail boasts stunning views and is widely regarded as one of the most beautiful entry points for hikers in the area. Its serene surroundings invite individuals to embark on a journey through nature's wonders, where they can marvel at the breathtaking landscapes that unfold along the way.
name: Sandy's Canyon Trail
address: Flagstaff, AZ 86001, USA

excerpt: Legendary, cross-country route, from Chicago to L.A., with iconic neon signs, gas stations & diners.
detail_description: Historic Route 66 is a legendary cross-country route that stretches from Chicago to Los Angeles, featuring iconic neon signs, gas stations, and diners along the way. This historic route passes through various locations such as Northern Arizona University, U.S. Naval Observatory, and the U.S., accessible via several routes including -17, -40, Routes 93, 89 and 89A.
name: Historic Rte 66

excerpt: Trendy hangout & local art gallery offering craft coffee, beer, wine & pastries, plus free Wi-Fi.
detail_description: This coffee shop is a flagstaff favorite with its delicious, specialty coffees and artsy vibes. It has three other locations throughout northern Arizona as well as coffee for wholesale. Live music is also regularly hosted here.
name: Firecreek Coffee Company
address: 22 Historic Rte 66, Flagstaff, AZ 86001, USA

excerpt: Cozy pick for espresso drinks & a breakfast-to-dinner veggie menu with vegan & gluten-free options.
detail_description: Macy's European Coffeehouse & Bakery is a beloved spot in Flagstaff, offering a cozy atmosphere and a diverse menu. Whether you're craving espresso drinks or looking for vegan and gluten-free options, Macy's has something for everyone. The cafe is known for its delicious pastries like the apple pie croissant and French cinnamon rolls, as well as hearty dishes such as biscuits and gravy.
name: Macy's European Coffeehouse & Bakery
address: 14 S Beaver St, Flagstaff, AZ 86001, USA

detail_description: This Flagstaff KOA is a great place to stay if you're in the area for a weekend getaway. The campground features plenty of space for tents, trailers, and RVs, as well as several amenities like an outdoor pool, playgrounds, and fishing opportunities. There's also a convenience store on-site should you need anything else while you're here.
name: Flagstaff KOA Holiday
address: 5803 US-89, Flagstaff, AZ 86004, USA

excerpt: 478-acre nature preserve featuring hiking, biking & horseback riding, plus wildlife & petroglyphs.
detail_description: Immerse yourself in the natural beauty and rich history of Picture Canyon Natural and Cultural Preserve, a 478-acre sanctuary offering a range of outdoor activities. Explore the picturesque landscape on foot, bike, or horseback while keeping an eye out for diverse wildlife species. Capture stunning photographs of beavers, otters, and various birds in their undisturbed habitat. Delve into the area's cultural heritage by discovering ancient petroglyphs etched into the rocks along the Tom Moody Trail.
name: Picture Canyon Natural and Cultural Preserve
address: 3920 N El Paso Flagstaff Rd, Flagstaff, AZ 86004, USA

excerpt: Vibrant joint with a salsa bar & ample plates of familiar Mexican fare, plus creative margaritas.
detail_description: Salsa Brava is a vibrant Mexican restaurant in Flagstaff, known for its handmade salsas and creative dishes that blend traditional Mexican and Southwestern flavors. The restaurant takes pride in using all-natural ingredients, including locally sourced produce from the Flagstaff Farmers Market. With a self-serve salsa bar and hot made-to-order food, Salsa Brava offers an authentic dining experience.
name: Salsa Brava
address: 2220 E Rte 66, Flagstaff, AZ 86004, USA

excerpt: Bright, casual locale showcasing a seasonal menu of artful American small plates & craft cocktails.
detail_description: Shift Kitchen & Bar is a bright and casual eatery located in Downtown Flagstaff, offering a seasonal menu of American small plates and craft cocktails. The restaurant, owned by a husband and wife culinary team, provides an intimate dining experience with only 34 seats, including an interactive chef's counter. In the morning, guests can enjoy decadent pastries and coffee, while the dinner menu features progressive dishes made with both familiar and exotic ingredients.
name: Shift Kitchen & Bar
address: 107 N San Francisco St #2, Flagstaff, AZ 86001, USA

excerpt: Easygoing spot with a walk-up & drive-thru window for hot dogs, burgers & other American eats.
detail_description: The Route 66 Dog Haus is a small and quaint breakfast restaurant with dog-friendly drive-thru windows. The food is fresh, affordable and includes items such as burgers, hot dogs, croissants and hashes. The workers are friendly and welcoming, asking if the dogs would like sausage patties on their breakfast sandwiches. Overall, this place is great for a cheap breakfast or quick bite to eat with your furry friend!
name: Route 66 Dog Haus
address: 1302 E Rte 66, Flagstaff, AZ 86001, USA

detail_description: Sinclair Wash is a popular trail that takes about 1 hour and 53 minutes to complete. It's well-loved for birding, hiking, and mountain biking, offering opportunities for solitude during quieter times of the day. The best months to visit are from April through October. This mostly flat dirt trail includes a labyrinth and starts at Fort Tuthill Park, ending at an intersection of the Arizona Trail.
name: Sinclair Wash
address: Flagstaff, AZ 86001, USA

excerpt: Relaxed rooms in a Route 66 motel with a Greek restaurant & grassy picnic area with BBQ grill.
detail_description: The Western Hills Motel is a classic 50s Route 66 motel with relaxed rooms and a Greek restaurant on-site. The neon sign featuring a team of horses pulling a covered wagon adds to its charm. While the rooms are somewhat outdated, they offer clean sheets and adequate WiFi. The friendly host and convenient location near businesses make it more than meets the eye, despite occasional train noise. With affordable rates and a nearby Mexican restaurant, it's a pleasant choice for travelers looking for simplicity and convenience.
name: Western Hills Motel
address: 1580 E Rte 66, Flagstaff, AZ 86001, USA

detail_description: Sweet Shoppe Candy Store is a charming old-fashioned candy store that offers a wide variety of sweet treats to satisfy any craving. From homemade fudge in classic and unique flavors to gourmet caramel apples, chocolate truffles, barks, and Italian gelato in the summer, there's something for everyone. The store also welcomes furry friends and offers special treats for pups alongside human favorites like macarons and caramels. Visitors can also explore an array of chocolate-covered items and unique soda flavors.
name: Sweet Shoppe Candy Store
address: 15 E Aspen Ave, Flagstaff, AZ 86001, USA

excerpt: Microbrewery in a former lumberyard building featuring a taproom, eatery & patio with a fire pit.
detail_description: Lumberyard Brewing Co is a microbrewery located in Flagstaff, Arizona, housed in a beautifully restored early 1900s lumber building. The brewery features a taproom, eatery, and patio with a fire pit for visitors to enjoy. Established by Winnie and Evan Hanseth, the brewery offers a variety of award-winning beers including 7 mainstay brews, seasonal selections, limited releases, and their latest creation - Hazy Angel IPA.
name: Lumberyard Brewing Co
address: 5 S San Francisco St, Flagstaff, AZ 86001, USA

detail_description: Embark on an adventure to the Flagstaff Area National Monuments, where nature and history intertwine across over 40,000 acres of stunning landscapes. This collective includes Walnut Canyon, Sunset Crater Volcano, and Wupatki National Monuments, each offering unique experiences. For those seeking a challenge, the Island Trail at Walnut Canyon features a rigorous one-mile hike with over 200 stairs leading into the canyon's depths.
name: Flagstaff Area National Monuments
address: 6400 US-89, Flagstaff, AZ 86004, USA

detail_description: The Schultz Creek Trail located in the northern part of Flagstaff is highly favored by mountain bikers and hikers alike. It offers a picturesque journey through the forest, providing ample shade for its visitors. The trail is deemed moderate by mountain bikers due to certain sections with rocky terrain, but they find it enjoyable when going downhill. This trail presents an excellent opportunity for both hiking enthusiasts and those who enjoy mountain biking, making it a popular choice among outdoor adventurers in the area.
name: Schultz Creek
address: Fort Valley, AZ 86001, USA
